# Cursor IDE Configuration Rules for Neural Child Project

# Rules
- When creating new files, always include a header with the file name, date, and a brief description of the file and what it does.
- Always write comments and docstrings in a professional and engaging way.
- Always update the CHANGELOG.md file with the latest changes.
- Always update the README.md file with the latest changes.
- Make suggestions for improvements and optimizations.
- Always include detailed error handling for LLM API interactions.
- Add debug logging for LLM requests and responses.
- Ensure compatibility with LM Studio's API format.

# Ollama Integration Rules
[ollama]
# API Configuration
base_url = "http://localhost:11434"
max_retries = 5
timeout_seconds = 60
backoff_factor = 1.5
stream_mode = false

# Model Settings
default_model = "deepseek-r1"
fallback_model = "neural-chat"
temperature_range = [0.1, 1.0]
max_tokens = 500

# Error Handling
require_health_check = true
require_fallback_responses = true
log_all_prompts = true
log_all_responses = true
enable_response_validation = true

# Performance
enable_response_caching = true
cache_duration_minutes = 30
enable_batch_processing = true
max_concurrent_requests = 3

